Program: The History Hour
Title: The division of Kashmir
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csypyy
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 19 Aug 2019
The origins of the crisis in Kashmir, the warnings ignored about 9/11 and the arrest of the notorious terror suspect Carlos the Jackal. Plus the invention in a British back garden of the daily disposable contact lens and how Dr Seuss taught America to read. Photo: Indian troops arriving in Kashmir in October 1947 (Getty Images) Show less